headlines.description: — With a large, loud contingent of Slovenia fans on hand, Luka Doncic wanted to give his countrymen a show.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's 35 points, 13 assists send Mavs past Cavs 120-112

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic flirted with another triple-double with 37 points, 13 rebounds and nine assists, helping the Denver Nuggets hold off the Indiana Pacers 125-118 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 37 points to lead Nuggets past Pacers 125-118

headlines.description: — Tomas Satoransky couldn't decide if this type of double-double was good or bad. It was certainly unusual.
headlines.shortLinkText: Satoransky's unusual double-double lifts Wizards past Magic

headlines.description: — An untimely losing streak has left the Miami Heat with some late-season competition for the Eastern Conference’s top seed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler scores 24 to help Heat fend off Celtics 106-98

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 14 of his 31 points in the fourth quarter and LaMelo Ball had 20 points and 15 rebounds to help lead the Charlotte Hornets past the New York Knicks 125-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Ball help Hornets to 125-114 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 12 points, 10 rebounds and a career-high 13 assists for his second career triple-double, Gary Trent Jr. scored 29 points and the Toronto Raptors strengthened their hold on sixth place in the Eastern Conference by beating the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam has triple-double, Raptors rout Timberwolves 125-102

headlines.description: — Davion Mitchell, Damian Jones and Trey Lyles scored 24 points each, and the Sacramento Kings outlasted the Houston Rockets for a 121-118 win Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings used balanced scoring attack to beat Rockets 121-118

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 41 points and eight assists, and the Atlanta Hawks rolled past the Oklahoma City Thunder 136-118 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 41 as Hawks top Thunder 136-118

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Tyus Jones scored 25 points and the Memphis Grizzlies edged the San Antonio Spurs 112-111 on Wednesday night to capture the Southwest Division title and clinch the No. 2 seed in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies edge Spurs 112-111, clinch No. 2 seed in West

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Chin-ups, lunges, blaring music and some good-natured banter at 10 p.m.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Paul deliver at end, Suns hold off Warriors 107-103

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum received a 90-second standing ovation in his first visit to Portland since a February trade to New Orleans, then scored 25 points to lead the Pelicans over the Trail Blazers 117-107 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum cheered in return, helps Pelicans beat Blazers
